---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SITE } from "../site";

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  name: `About ${SITE.name}`,
  url: new URL("/about/", SITE.url).toString(),
  publisher: { "@type": "Organization", name: SITE.name, url: SITE.url },
  author: { "@type": "Person", name: SITE.author, url: SITE.authorUrl },
};
---

<Base
  title={`About · ${SITE.name}`}
  description="welldun is a one-builder lab for multi-tenant software + AI infrastructure. About the projects, the through-line, and me."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="wrap">
    <header class="article-head rise">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>welldun</h1>
      <p class="dek">Building at the seam of software and AI — and writing up how it works.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose rise rise-2">
      <p>
        <strong>welldun</strong> is where I build and document practical
        <strong>software + AI infrastructure</strong>. The pattern across everything here is
        the same: <strong>multi-tenant by default</strong>, bring-your-own-keys, with security
        and reliability treated as features rather than afterthoughts — and AI used where it
        genuinely earns its place, not as decoration.
      </p>

      <h2>What's being built</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Entity platform</strong> (<em>Drafting Table</em>) — a platform where each
          customer defines their own entities, fields, and relationships, and the system
          generates the storage, validation, APIs, and analytics from those definitions.
          No per-customer code. <a href="/series/drafting-table/">Read the series →</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Voice infra</strong> — a Retell-style, multi-tenant voice-calling backend:
          STT + LLM + TTS orchestrated end to end, bring-your-own provider keys (stored with
          envelope encryption), consumable by any third party over a plain API.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Email infra</strong> — a multi-tenant email-sending API: connect your own
          SendGrid/Resend keys, send through one reliable surface, with a Postgres work queue,
          circuit breaking, idempotent writes, and signed delivery webhooks.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Workflow automation</strong> — a visual builder (React Flow) over a durable
          execution engine, where adding a custom block is a single file.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        The writing here is the running field notebook for these — the architecture bets, the
        gotchas, and the things that only show up once you ship and measure.
      </p>

      <h2>Me</h2>
      <p>
        I'm {SITE.author}. Previously at <strong>Stripe</strong>; now founder of
        <strong>Valyx</strong>, a B2B startup. I like building systems and taking them apart in
        writing — the kind of write-up I wish existed when I was figuring the thing out.
      </p>

      <p>
        Reach me at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>, or follow along via the
        <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
